body.description: Powered by Intel Core X-Series processors, the Asus Prime X299-A II design for those who prefer to put their high-core-count processors to more productive. It combines cutting-edge performance with signature features, including a powerful VRM tailored for overclocking, intuitive cooling control, next-gen connectivity, and extensive customization. Features 12 IR3555 power stages, DDR4 4266 MHz, triple M.2, USB 3.2 Gen 2 Type-C and Aura Sync RGB lighting.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Features Best in Class Power Design Equipped with an enhanced power solution that includes 12 power stages that line up neatly along the top edge of the PCBProCool II Power Connectors ensure flush contact with the PSU power lines and have a metal armour for improved heat dissipation. Unrivaled Memory Performance Its quad-channel memory controller supports up to 256 GB of DDR4 memory across eight slots. With optimized trace layout, the Prime X299-A II can hit memory speeds up to DDR4 4266 MHz or beyond

Cool to the core It comes equipped with active VRM heatsink, onboard M.2 heatsinks, an array of fan headers that are controllable via FanXpert 4, a reinforced back plate, options for water pump and AIO headers. Ultimate connectivity Intel Optane memory ready, Intel VROC support, dual M.2 support, and USB 3.2 Gen Type-C

Tune it your way With ASUS AI Overclocking, 5-way Optimization and UEFI Bios to provide comprehensive controls form the foundation of the ASUS Prime series. It packs flexible tools to tune every aspect of your system to deliver the performance that you desire. DIY Friendly Pre-mount I/O ShieldFlexKey- a multiple-purpose reset buttonBIOS Flashback - supports USB BIOS Flashback, which can perform low-level firmware updates using only a power supply and a USB stick with the required file.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Versatility for Enthusiast Systems!
reviews.reviewText: The Asus Prime X299-A II ATX Motherboard has proven to be an outstanding choice for my high-performance system. As an enthusiast seeking powerful performance and versatility, this motherboard has exceeded my expectations in every aspect.First and foremost, the compatibility with Intel X299 processors and LGA 2066 socket ensures optimal performance and future-proofing for my system. It supports a wide range of Intel Core X-Series processors, providing exceptional power and speed for demanding tasks such as gaming, content creation, and heavy multitasking.The Prime X299-A II boasts an impressive array of features. The robust VRM design and advanced power delivery ensure stable and efficient performance, even under heavy loads. The motherboard supports up to 128GB of DDR4 memory, allowing for ample capacity and exceptional speeds.One of the standout features of this motherboard is its extensive connectivity options. It features multiple PCIe slots, SATA ports, USB ports, and M.2 slots, providing flexibility for expansion and accommodating a wide range of peripherals and storage devices. The inclusion of USB 3.2 Gen 2 and Thunderbolt 3 support further enhances the connectivity capabilities, allowing for lightning-fast data transfer speeds and seamless connections with external devices.The build quality of the Prime X299-A II is exceptional. The motherboard feels solid and well-constructed, ensuring durability and longevity. The UEFI BIOS is user-friendly and offers extensive customization options, making it easy to fine-tune the system according to my preferences.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This MOBO is stable and easy to install.
reviews.reviewText: Had only one issue with this MOBO. Tried to install a SADA SSD M.2 stick in the wrong socket. SADA SSD M.2 needs to be installed in the upright M.2 socket. Ended up installing an NVMe SSD M.2 stick as well. Very fast I/O. Installed the latest BIOS. My RAM was apparently to slow to overclock. I'll update that later. The MOBO does everything I need it to do and them some. Highly recommended.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 22, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Do not buy this motherboard
reviews.reviewText: The motherboard came with bent pins on the cpu socket and this voids the warranty even know I did not bend them.When I called tech support the person on the phone which barely spoke English kept repeating to me that the warranty is void due to bent pins and would not let me talk to a higher official. I have been building computers for close to 20 years and this is the first motherboard I have had a problem with. ASUS is no longer a quality product so I would recommend that no one ever buys a ASUS product. I will never buy another ASUS motherboard.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 29, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Using on a 10900x i9 with 20 cores - works great, but yet to enable M.2. with 2 WD 1TB drives
reviews.reviewText: Using on a 10900x i9 with 20 thread cores - works great, tested overclocking, with Crosair 2x32 gb rams on one slot on each side (still 6 free). Thermaltake 3-fan liquid cooler,TT 850 rgb fan on demand power supply, Asus 3 fan super 6gb graphics card with fan on demand(fan only runs when there is heat on both the graphic and the power supply) - RGB synced with TT's controller and i have to buy both the 3 pin and 4 pin rgb connectors for asus software to sync between all the devices (except ram from 32*2 crosair - which i am crazy about not to buy anything else)so far one thing i cannot figure out is to enable even the m.2. disks as standard, as it says bios does not support 1 TB WD black drives. i wanted to setup a raid 1 with 2 WD 1TB drives. both does not come down as Hard raids / even the disks are not readable.

reviews.reviewText: Was fairly easy to install & configure.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 2, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very Stable. Excellent features, easy to add WI-FI/BT6.
reviews.reviewText: This replaced an ASUS X299 Deluxe board which was damaged by a liquid spill. While less expensive than the Prime Deluxe, it is actually a better fit for me. Adding a WI-FI ax/BT6 internal M.2 card was a snap (I used the Intel kit which includes the back plate and antennas) and the board layout is an improvement over the original Prime Delux I had. I would not hesitate to purchase this board again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 1, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Had some tech issues, but seller was great.
reviews.reviewText: I had to return this mobo and get a new one, or so i thought. I was able to return at A Kohls and get a new one sent out from Amazon directly. Shipping and the return process was lightning fast and easy. The mobo would get hung on boot up while my Nvidia 1660 super GPU was installed, even with the replacement. Turns out I just needed to boot with no GPU installed once, then power down and restart with GPU installed. Booted up, and allowed me to update bios via internet. It is a powerful mobo for the money, and the AI overclock is great. I love it. highly recomended.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on October 15, 2021
reviews.reviewText: Unfortunately, the motherboard I received was defective, with the error "USB over current detected" being report by BIOS, with no USB device connected to the motherboard.I suspect this may have been used before I received it.Not a happy customer.

reviews.reviewTitle: Handily took the place of a failed MSI Pro X299 Motherboard
reviews.reviewText: Just over a year into running an MSI Pro X299 as a video editing station... it died. Send the motherboard away and after 16 days in the hands of their Repair Center, I don't even have an ETA as to when it'll be repaired or replaced and sent back to me. Sort of KNOWING that this was likely to happen, AND my flawless track-record with Asus motherboards, I ordered the X299-A II, connected everything to it and I was up and running with only a few MSI startup items to delete and some Asus specific items to install. Back to editing as easy as that. Stress test benchmark even produced a better score than the same processor in the MSI MoBo. Excellent Asus X299 board.

Working great so far with all memory slots occupied and under relatively heavy load every day. One thing though, is that whenever I try to install Aura Sync the system crashes and sometimes even kills the OS so I had to rollback. Other than that though, works great.
